Instruction: With all modules connected and all switches ON, use a voltmeter referenced to the power‑supply negative to measure the voltage on each of the two conductors entering the load module. Confirm one is at about +12 V and the other at 0 V. Then, inside the load module, measure the voltage across the series diode (anode to cathode) and across the main lamp terminals while the battery is installed, to determine whether the diode is forward‑biased and whether supply voltage is actually appearing across the lamp branch.
