TYPE: Test,
TARGET: Through‑path of each control module (CM2–CM8, sequentially),
DESCRIPTION: With all modules connected as originally and all switches ON, keep the voltmeter reference on the power‑supply negative. For each control module from CM2 to CM8 in turn, probe its two incoming conductors and its two outgoing conductors. Record, for each side, which conductor is at +12 V and which at 0 V. Also measure the voltage between the two conductors on the upstream side and then between the two conductors on the downstream side to confirm whether ~12 V exists across each pair. This will locate the first module position at which the +12 V line disappears (both conductors go to 0 V or float), indicating where the open circuit or mis‑wiring in the series path resides.,
