2026-04-16 12:19:58 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 3 input (+) terminal / internal connection'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that +12 V is present up to the input of Control Module 3, but its output (+) conductor is at 0 V and all downstream modules and the load see 0 V. Continuity testing (with battery removed) reveals an open circuit between the CM3 + input cable terminal and both the switch and the + output terminal, while the path from the switch to the + output is continuous. Therefore the fault is localized to the CM3 +12 V input side: either the input (+) terminal itself or the short internal trace/wire from that terminal to the switch/through‑path is open or otherwise not making contact. Repair or replacement of Control Module 3 (specifically its + input terminal/connection) should restore +12 V to the downstream modules and allow the lamp to operate when all switches are ON.'
